Picked up this @edwardandsons "Road's End" Shells - Cheddar Style about a month ago in my local store on sale as its best by the end of the month. After buying,, I looked into Edward & Sons and they're a food broker of organic food and tons of vegan things, check them out, they broker really recognizable vegan goods that I've seen in every health food store I've ever been to.

Sooo, there's something about being home alone that makes me really not feel like cooking (literally a shocking rare event) After cooking it the way all boxed Mac N Cheese is cooked.... in true me fashion, I added a bunch of frozen peas and a handful of raw baby spinach and some Bomba Sauce on top as usual). 

This is not your Kraft or Velveeta -  it's earthy, satisfying yet mild - something that you can feel good about feeding someone who has a sensitive stomach. It is a pretty standard roux of nooch, mylk onion powder and other spices but its not a salt bomb at all, so its advised to add toppings.

 I will say though, that since this Mac N "Chreese" is meant for children, they do a good job of adding vegan B vitamins the way that milk & oj companies add calcium and vitamin D. 

I could easily have made this myself without the sauce packet butttttt im not in the mood. And I ran out of Nooch, the literal second ingredient in the sauce. So, for a boxed meal, I feel like this is pretty aces all around with organic ingredients and a clean flavor. And more time with my mipi girl ğŸˆ ğŸ˜» less time checking the stove and washing dishes ğŸ¤Ÿ

